Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.080 --> 00:00:04.790
Veronica Porsche Ali is an American actress
and the former wife of boxing legend Muhammad

00:00:04.790 --> 00:00:06.220
Ali.

00:00:06.220 --> 00:00:12.030
Porsche was born in Louisiana on December
16, 1955 to Ethel and Horace Porche and is

00:00:12.030 --> 00:00:14.610
of Louisiana Creole descent.

00:00:14.610 --> 00:00:19.789
She attended Holy Rosary Catholic boarding
school in Lafayette, Louisiana before moving

00:00:19.789 --> 00:00:25.590
with her parents to Echo Park, California,
a suburb of Los Angeles.

00:00:25.590 --> 00:00:31.369
She graduated from Belmont High School in
Los Angeles in 1973 and attended the University

00:00:31.369 --> 00:00:35.240
of Southern California, majoring in Pre-Medicine.

00:00:35.240 --> 00:00:40.760
She was the third wife of American boxer Muhammad
Ali, and is the mother of his two daughters,

00:00:40.760 --> 00:00:46.030
actress and undefeated professional boxer
Laila Ali and author Hana Yasmeen Ali.

00:00:46.030 --> 00:00:50.390
They were married at the Presidential Compound
in N'Sele according to the Islamic tradition..

00:00:50.390 --> 00:00:56.050
Ali and Porsche began a relationship in 1974
while in Kinshasa, Zaire when Porsche was

00:00:56.050 --> 00:00:58.050
18 years old.

00:00:58.050 --> 00:01:02.030
Porsche was one of the four poster girls who
had promoted the Rumble in the Jungle fight

00:01:02.030 --> 00:01:04.850
in Zaire versus George Foreman.

00:01:04.850 --> 00:01:09.610
Porsche and Ali were then married in Los Angeles
in the summer of 1977.

00:01:09.610 --> 00:01:13.090
They divorced in December 1986.

00:01:13.090 --> 00:01:17.440
Porsche studied acting at the Beverly Hills
Playhouse to overcome shyness and had limited

00:01:17.440 --> 00:01:19.890
experience as an actress.

00:01:19.890 --> 00:01:25.430
She played a tour guide, Ranger Emily, in
the 1986 film Terror on Alcatraz and made

00:01:25.430 --> 00:01:30.200
a cameo appearance in "Freedom Road" starring
Ali and Kris Kristofferson.

00:01:30.200 --> 00:01:36.930
She co-hosted a segment of "Good Morning,
New York" and appeared as herself in a made-for-TV

00:01:36.930 --> 00:01:39.880
documentary, Intimate Portrait: Laila Ali.

00:01:39.880 --> 00:01:44.610
In the movie Ali, starring Will Smith, the
role of Veronica Porsche Ali was played by

00:01:44.610 --> 00:01:46.540
Michael Michele.

00:01:46.540 --> 00:01:50.610
Both Porsche and Ali commented that their
relationship and other occurrences were not

00:01:50.610 --> 00:01:52.670
accurately portrayed.

00:01:52.670 --> 00:01:57.320
Personal life
In 1992, Porsche-Ali married jazz artist and

00:01:57.320 --> 00:02:00.070
stage actor Carl Anderson.

00:02:00.070 --> 00:02:05.140
Anderson was probably most noted for his portrayal
of Judas Iscariot in the hit musical Jesus

00:02:05.140 --> 00:02:09.360
Christ Superstar and the 1973 movie of the
same name.

00:02:09.360 --> 00:02:15.360
Veronica and Carl traveled together in the
mid 1990s when Carl reprised his role and

00:02:15.360 --> 00:02:17.880
toured the United States.

00:02:17.880 --> 00:02:21.360
Anderson died of leukemia in 2004.

00:02:21.360 --> 00:02:27.150
In May 2007, Veronica appeared with her two
daughters, Laila and Hana, on the American

00:02:27.150 --> 00:02:30.090
TV series Dancing with the Stars.

